    This class creates a dialog which allows the user to create, open, and modify Process schedules. For a new process, user can chooser from available system knowledge processes.

      • updateDialogProcessScheduleLoaded

        private void updateDialogProcessScheduleLoaded()
        This updates the process scheduler with a loaded process schedule. Enables the copy, save (if a PS file already exists, save as, remove process, and file unload ,menu items. Displays the process, time step, and the choosen units for this scheduled process.

      • updateDialogNoProcessScheduleLoaded

        private void updateDialogNoProcessScheduleLoaded()
        If no process schedule basically clears out the process schedule dialog by disabling previous, next buttons, and menu items for save, save as, copy, remove and unload. It clears out the process name and time step labels.
